definitions: not able to be used, obtained, or accessed at the present time
not free to see or meet people due to other commitments
examples: The product is currently unavailable in stores nationwide
This feature is unavailable on older phone models
The doctor is unavailable for appointments this week
She was unavailable for comment after the announcement

definitions: not able to be prevented, avoided, or ignored due to circumstances
certain to happen or be experienced because of inherent necessity
examples: Traffic delays were unavoidable due to the accident
Some mistakes are unavoidable when learning something new
Death and taxes are unavoidable aspects of life
Meeting your in-laws is an unavoidable part of marriage

definitions: having no knowledge or consciousness of a situation or fact
examples: She was unaware of the danger lurking nearby
The students were unaware that class was cancelled

definitions: not steady or stable in physical position or emotional state
emotionally or mentally disturbed showing erratic or unstable behavior
not arranged in equal or proper proportions lacking symmetry
examples: The unbalanced load made the washing machine shake
He felt unbalanced after spinning around too quickly
Her unbalanced behavior worried her family and friends
The villain was portrayed as unbalanced and dangerous
The unbalanced diet lacked essential vitamins and minerals
The painting looked unbalanced with everything on one side

definitions: not able to be endured or tolerated due to extreme intensity
examples: The unbearable heat forced everyone to stay indoors
The pain became unbearable without medication

definitions: not able to be defeated or surpassed in competition or quality
offering such good value that nothing else can match it
examples: Their team seems unbeatable after winning ten straight games
Her record time remains unbeatable after twenty years
These prices are unbeatable during our clearance sale
The restaurant offers unbeatable quality for the price

definitions: not having been defeated or lost in competition or contest
examples: The team remains unbeaten after twelve consecutive matches
The champion boxer retired unbeaten throughout her career

definitions: not fitting or appropriate for a person's position or character
not attractive or flattering in appearance or style
examples: Such behavior is unbecoming of a professional athlete
Using that language is unbecoming for a teacher
That hairstyle is rather unbecoming on most people
The dress was unbecoming and made her look frumpy

definitions: happening or existing without the knowledge of the person specified
examples: Unbeknown to her parents, she had quit college
The changes occurred unbeknown to most employees

definitions: happening or existing without the knowledge of the person mentioned
examples: Unbeknownst to the children, their parents planned a surprise
He had been promoted unbeknownst to his colleagues

definitions: showing no unfair preference or prejudice toward particular opinions or sides
examples: The judge must remain unbiased throughout the trial
We need an unbiased opinion from someone outside

definitions: not yet born but existing in the womb as a fetus
examples: The unborn child could already hear its mother's voice
New laws protect the rights of unborn children

definitions: not tied, fastened, or held by physical restraints or bonds
not subject to limits, restrictions, or controls of any kind
referring to printed pages not fastened together in book form
examples: The prisoner's hands were unbound after the interrogation
Her hair flowed unbound in the summer breeze
His creativity seemed unbound by conventional thinking patterns
Their enthusiasm was unbound after winning the championship
The manuscript remained unbound until the final edits
These unbound pages need to be properly assembled

definitions: having no limits or boundaries in extent, size, or enthusiasm
examples: Her unbounded enthusiasm inspired everyone on the team
The universe appears unbounded in its vast expanse

definitions: having no branches extending from the main stem or structure
examples: The unbranched trunk rose straight toward the sky
This unbranched molecule has a simple linear structure

definitions: not able to be broken or damaged even under extreme force
not able to be violated, ended, or made invalid under any circumstances
examples: The new phone screen claims to be virtually unbreakable
Their bond seemed unbreakable after years of friendship
They made an unbreakable promise to stay together
The encryption code was designed to be unbreakable

definitions: not controlled or restrained showing no limits in expression or behavior
examples: His unbridled enthusiasm sometimes overwhelmed his colleagues at meetings
The novel depicts unbridled passion between the main characters

definitions: remaining whole and intact without any cracks, breaks, or damage
continuing without pause, interruption, or change over a period
examples: The vase remained unbroken despite falling off the shelf
All the eggs arrived unbroken in their protective packaging
She maintained unbroken concentration for three hours straight
The family kept an unbroken tradition for fifty years

definitions: strange or mysterious in an unsettling way suggesting supernatural origin
so remarkable or exact as to seem beyond normal human ability
examples: There was an uncanny silence in the abandoned house
She felt an uncanny presence watching her movements
He has an uncanny ability to predict market trends
The resemblance between the twins was absolutely uncanny

definitions: not subject to a maximum limit especially in financial contexts
having had the cap or cover removed from a container
examples: The company offers uncapped commission for top salespeople
Internet plans with uncapped data are becoming rare
She left the pen uncapped and it dried out
The uncapped bottle spilled during the car ride

definitions: not showing sympathy, concern, or interest in others' feelings or welfare
examples: His uncaring attitude hurt his children deeply over time
The uncaring response from officials angered the victims' families

definitions: not subjected to censorship with all original content left intact
examples: The documentary showed uncensored footage from the war
The uncensored version of the book contained controversial passages

definitions: not able to be relied on or known definitely with accuracy
not feeling confident or sure about something showing hesitation
examples: The election outcome remains uncertain until all votes count
Weather forecasts are uncertain beyond the next few days
She felt uncertain about accepting the job offer abroad
His uncertain voice revealed his lack of preparation

definitions: released from chains or other physical restraints allowing free movement
examples: The unchained dog ran joyfully around the open yard
His unchained creativity produced remarkable works of art

definitions: not disputed, questioned, or opposed by anyone remaining accepted without contest
examples: Her authority went unchallenged for over a decade
The theory remained unchallenged until new evidence emerged

definitions: not made or become different remaining in the original state
examples: The town remained unchanged despite decades passing by slowly
Her feelings for him were unchanged after all these years

definitions: remaining the same over time showing no variation or alteration
examples: The unchanging landscape provided a sense of timeless peace
His unchanging routine helped him maintain mental stability daily

definitions: not typical or usual for a particular person or thing's normal behavior
examples: His angry outburst was completely uncharacteristic of his personality
The team's poor performance was uncharacteristic this season overall

definitions: not recorded on a map or chart representing unknown territory
not yet explored or experienced representing unfamiliar situations or fields
examples: The expedition ventured into uncharted regions of the rainforest
Ancient sailors feared sailing into uncharted waters beyond maps
Starting a business meant entering uncharted territory for her
The research explores uncharted areas of quantum physics theory

definitions: not examined, verified, or investigated for accuracy or problems
allowed to continue or increase without restraint or control
examples: The unchecked data contained numerous errors and inconsistencies throughout
Unchecked luggage poses serious security risks at airports nowadays
Unchecked population growth strains natural resources and infrastructure systems
His unchecked anger eventually destroyed all his personal relationships

definitions: not having an advanced or modern level of cultural and social development
examples: Their uncivilized behavior at dinner shocked the other guests
Some consider eating with hands uncivilized in formal settings

definitions: not claimed or collected by the rightful owner or recipient
examples: Unclaimed luggage is auctioned after ninety days at airports
The lottery prize remained unclaimed for several months surprisingly

definitions: not assigned to a particular class, category, or group yet
referring to information not designated as secret or confidential
examples: These unclassified documents still need proper filing and organization
Several unclassified species were discovered during the expedition recently
The report contains only unclassified information available to public
Unclassified materials can be freely shared between departments now

definitions: dirty or contaminated not meeting standards of cleanliness or purity
examples: The unclean water caused illness throughout the entire village
He felt unclean after working in the dusty attic

definitions: not gathered, picked up, or claimed from where it was left
examples: Uncollected mail piled up during their month-long vacation abroad
The uncollected garbage attracted rats to the neighborhood streets

definitions: not pledged or bound to a particular course of action
not showing dedication or loyalty to a cause or relationship
examples: Several uncommitted delegates could swing the nomination either way
She remained uncommitted about her college choice until May
His uncommitted attitude frustrated his teammates during practice sessions
Uncommitted volunteers rarely last long in demanding charity work

definitions: not often seen, found, or experienced being relatively rare
remarkably great or intense in degree surpassing what is usual
examples: Snow is uncommon in this region during autumn months
It's uncommon to find such dedication in young employees
She showed uncommon bravery in rescuing the drowning child
The artist displayed uncommon talent from an early age

definitions: not able to compete successfully against others in quality or price
examples: Their uncompetitive prices drove customers to shop elsewhere regularly
The team became uncompetitive after losing their star players

definitions: not brought to an end or conclusion remaining in partial state
examples: The uncompleted project cost the company millions in losses
Her uncompleted degree haunted her throughout her successful career

definitions: simple and straightforward without unnecessary complexity or difficulty to understand
examples: The recipe was uncomplicated enough for beginning cooks to follow
She preferred an uncomplicated lifestyle without drama or stress

definitions: showing an unwillingness to make concessions or accept less than demanded
examples: Her uncompromising standards ensured only the best quality products
The director's uncompromising vision created a masterpiece of cinema

definitions: showing a lack of worry or interest about something appearing indifferent
examples: He seemed unconcerned about the approaching deadline for submission
The cat remained unconcerned as the dog barked loudly

definitions: not subject to any conditions or limitations being absolute and complete
examples: Parents often give unconditional love to their children always
The company demanded unconditional surrender from its rival competitor

definitions: not yet proved to be true or officially verified as accurate
examples: Unconfirmed reports suggest the merger might happen next month
The death toll remains unconfirmed as rescue efforts continue

definitions: not joined or linked together physically, logically, or by relationship
examples: The two incidents appear completely unconnected despite happening simultaneously
These unconnected wires need proper installation for safety reasons

definitions: not overcome, defeated, or brought under control remaining independent or victorious
examples: The mountain peak remained unconquered for another fifty years
Her unconquered spirit inspired others facing similar challenges daily

definitions: not guided by conscience being unreasonably excessive or shockingly unfair
going beyond all reasonable limits being excessive in amount or degree
examples: The lawyer charged unconscionable fees to desperate clients repeatedly
It's unconscionable to ignore suffering when you can help
The company made unconscionable profits during the crisis period
Waiting three hours for service is absolutely unconscionable here

definitions: not consolidated or unified into a single coherent mass or system
examples: The unconsolidated sediments shifted dangerously during the earthquake yesterday
Several unconsolidated departments operated independently without coordination necessary

definitions: not in accordance with or authorized by a country's constitution
examples: The court ruled the new law unconstitutional and void
Restricting free speech in this way is clearly unconstitutional
